budget committee told reporters the implication that republicans 
are unanimously behind something i dont think is true and robert 
strauss the democratic lawyer who cochairs the commission with 
lewis said there are substantial differences among republicans 
lewis also said a minority on the panel might put out a 
dissenting report 
i would think theres a good chance that might be the case 
strauss said after tuesdays meeting 
the views expressed tuesday made it seem ever less likely that 
the panel created in late 1987 to find a bipartisan longrange 
solution to the governments colossal red ink problem would 
accomplish its goal 
tuesdays hourlong session focused on the nations savings and 
