contracts he made an employees wife who had an indian relative in 
her ancestry a 51 percent owner of his company 
she was a housewife he said he said she never participated 
in company business except to sign papers when necessary 
on tuesday gevene savala a kaibab paiute indian from arizona 
told the panel she was made president and invested her life savings 
in a road construction company run by her mexicanamerican husband 
who funneled his business to a larger nonindian firm 
now her company savala asphalt and construction enterprises 
