city of tangshan ended a 12year effort to find housing for victims 
of the most disastrous earthquake this century an official report 
said wednesday 
xinhua state news agency quoted mayor chen liyou as saying 
reconstruction of the devastated northeastern city was completed 
when the last families were transferred from temporary shelters it 
gave no date for the final move 
the july 28 1976 quake measured 78 on the richter scale and 
killed 242000 people it destroyed 97 percent of buildings in the 
city of 1 million 
chen said the government has spent 135 billion on constructions 
since 1979 
more than 200000 apartments have replaced makeshift homes of 
brick broken tile and plastic sheeting that housed most city 
residents for years after the quake 
xinhua quoted one man who was buried under rubble for six hours 
as saying he feels safe because his new apartment has been built to 
withstand quakes of up to 80 on the richter scale 
</TEXT>
