typical citizens 
while ordinary soviets wait in long lines for items such as 
coffee detergent fruit vegetables and chocolate the elite can 
have such things delivered or pick them up at stores that are 
offlimits to average citizens 
kremlin leaders and their families also are assigned apartments 
that are deluxe and spacious by soviet standards 
