<TEXT>
after 16 months of fruitless negotiations the 
contract dispute between eastern airlines and its machinists appears 
to be heading toward a 30day deadline and a possible walkout by 
easterns largest union 
on tuesday the financially hurting airline rejected binding 
arbitration nearly as soon as the offer was made by the national 
mediation board 
under the federal boards rule rejection of binding arbitration 
by either side leads to a 30day coolingoff period talks 
continue with mediators but if no settlement is reached the union 
can strike and the company can impose the conditions of its last 
contract offer 
