compaq computer corp said wednesday it recorded an 88 percent 
profit increase in the last quarter of 1988 capping a year in which 
the personal computer maker became the first startup company to 
achieve 2 billion in revenue in as little as six years 
just one year earlier houstonbased compaq attained 1 billion 
in revenue faster than any company built from scratch it previously 
ascended to the ranks of the fortune 500 in record time 
strong worldwide sales of our entire product line contributed 
both to the years and to the quarters strong performance rod 
canion the president and chief executive said in a statement 
international sales excluding canada contributed 39 percent of 
compaqs yearly revenue the company said 
compaq founded early in 1982 grew up as a maker of personal 
computers compatible with international business machines corps 
line it reached adulthood in 1987 when ibm switched to its personal 
system2 line and compaq chose to stick with the old standard 
a frontpage headline in a recent issue of info world a trade 
publication said compaq vying to become the ibm of the 90s 
that is somewhat of an overstatement ibm remains nearly 30 times 
the size of compaq and its revenue growth alone last year was twice 
compaqs overall revenue 
still at least in the field of personal computers compaq is 
trying to portray itself as the preserver of industry standards a 
role once held by ibm but ibm remains a formidable rival 
compaqs latest challenge is that ibms new pc line is slowly but 
surely expanding its share of the market while the extension to the 
old ibm standard promoted by compaq and other ibm rivals is still on 
the drawing boards 
canion and his partners began designing their first personal 
computer in february 1982 sales began in 1983 when the year was 
completed they had tallied sales of 1112 million an american 
business record 
compaq reached the fortune 500 in 1985 and achieved its first 
billiondollar year in 1987 
