<TEXT>
ryder system inc announced wednesday that it will 
buy back up to 15 percent of its stock and is considering selling 
four subsidiaries to refocus on its core transportation businesses 
the move was welcomed on wall street where ryder stock rose 
1125 to close at 28125 on the new york stock exchange 
this is very good news for the stock good news for the 
company said andrew geller a transportation analyst for 
provident national bank in philadelphia 
the planned 2year repurchase of up to 12 million of its 80 
million outstanding shares would cost the transportation and 
insurance company around 324 million based on tuesdays closing 
price of 27 a share 
but miamibased ryder expects to make a net gain of more than 
100 million by selling units that represent less than 5 percent of 
its total assets said m anthony burns ryders chairman president 
and chief executive officer 
we are selling businesses that havent met our financial 
objectives burns said in a statement 
the investment firm morgan stanley amp co has been engaged to 
explore the possible sale of ryders insurance management services 
division which includes managing general insurance agencies in 
florida alabama and texas two reinsurance companies and a 
reinsurance broker 
while the division has been a quality provider of services to 
the insurance market and a good profit contributor it does not have 
an important strategic fit with ryder systems core business and is 
probably more valuable to another company burns said 
the company also is considering the sale of ryder international 
freight and customs services inc a freight forwarding and customs 
brokerage company us packing and shipping co a freight assembly 
and distribution company and ryder freight system a fulltruckload 
common carrier 
we want to put a sharper focus on growing our highway 
transportation and aviation services core businesses burns said 
these other businesses probably have more value and a brighter 
future in the hands of other owners 
the moves continue efforts that started six months ago to reduce 
costs and improve asset utilization ryder said nearly 900 people 
have been laid off out of a total workforce of 43000 the number of 
ryder truck rental district offices has been cut from 105 to 97 and 
the aircraft services division which leases planes has been split 
in two 
burns said no new layoffs are expected 
ryders aircraft leasing business is by far its fastestgrowing 
sector and its vehicle leasing also accounts for a large share of 
revenue geller said 
the other parts of their business are solidly profitable but 
didnt really fit with the rest of these other services he said 
merrill lynch analyst john kalmbach in new york also welcomed the 
ryder moves the end result will be a somewhat smaller company 
with a narrower focus disposing of companies that are not 
individually very large and do not mean that much to the company in 
the long run he said 
the stock buyback to be arranged by salomon brothers inc will 
begin after ryder announces its 1988 financial results later this 
month and will be financed through borrowing burns said 
