<TEXT>
a special committee of the chicago mercantile 
exchange named the president of the futures industrys 
selfregulatory organization to advise the panel in its review of 
trading practices targeted by a sweeping federal fraud investigation 
the ninemember committee appointed robert wilmouth president of 
the chicagobased national futures association to assist in the 
review of trading procedure and policy said merc spokesman andrew 
yemma 
the committee held its first meeting wednesday a closed session 
expected to be the first in a series to discuss trading rules and 
procedures 
separately in washington the staff of the commodity futures 
trading commission recommended approval of the mercs proposed 
globex electronic trading system a key element in the exchanges 
move to set up afterhours global futures trading electronic 
trading also is seen by some as helping police improper activity by 
more closely monitoring deals 
the commission the federal agency that regulates the futures 
industry was expected to vote on the proposal thursday 
also the house agriculture committee designated rep glenn 
english dokla to direct a congressional investigation into 
trading practices in the futures and options markets 
english chairman of the panels subcommittee on conservation 
credit and rural development said the probe would focus on the 
cftcs regulation of the markets and on the selfregulating ability 
of the markets themselves 
the merc established its review panel following disclosure of a 
twoyear undercover federal probe of alleged widespread fraud and 
illegal trading practices in the chicago futures markets 
one practice under increasing scrutiny has been dual trading in 
which traders can buy and sell for themselves and their customers 
simultaneously 
the longtime practice is legal but critics say it invites abuse 
of the traditional openoutcry style of commodities trading in 
which traders use shouts and hand signals to buy and sell futures 
contracts in exchange trading pits 
karsten mahlmann chairman of the chicago board of trade 
indicated at a closed traders meeting tuesday that the exchange may 
reassess dual trading in light of the burgeoning scandal 
and in wednesdays editions the wall street journal reported 
that abs partners widely regarded as the most powerful group of 
brokers at the merc has banned dual trading by its members to avoid 
an appearance of conflict of interest 
none of the abs traders returned telephone requests wednesday 
afternoon for comment on the report 
such a move would be a further indication of how key futures 
market players may be trying to forestall possibly stronger 
government restrictions of their business in the wake of the fraud 
probe 
it also may indicate how dual trading could end up as the 
scapegoat of any attempted inhouse damage control much as 
computerized program trading became the target of voluntary 
restrictions among a number of major wall street firms following the 
october 1987 stock market crash 
broker groups such as abs employ brokers in different exchange 
trading pits where commodities futures contracts are actually 
bought and sold and split losses and profits with their members 
abs partners includes 24 brokers and other members and is 
controlled by maury a kravitz and james j kaulentis two of the 
mercs wealthiest and most powerful brokers the journal reported 
kravitz is a longtime friend and former law partner of leo 
melamed the powerful chairman of the mercs executive committee and 
a key figure in the exchanges growth in financial futures trading 
the newspaper stated 
in endorsing approval of the mercantile exchanges globex system 
the cftc staff recommended that globex trading initialy be limited 
to futures contracts on the australian dollar british pound 
canadian dollar west german mark swiss franc japanese yen 
eurodollar us treasury bills and gold 
globex developed by reuters holding plc is an electronic system 
which beginning this fall would be used before and after regular 
exchange hours 
eventually all of the exchanges contracts would be eligible for 
globex trading 
